      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1A">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> A. General Provisions</a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>Upon enrollment, all bonafide pupils and students are required to strictly observe the rules and regulations
                of the school as contained in this student handbook and with other directives issued by school authorities,
                and shall be held accountable for any failure to comply with such rules and regulations.</li>
              <li>Parents and guardians are advised to be aware of the contents of this student handbook for their information
                and proper guidance. Promotion, vandalism, hazing or maybe suspended or expelled from the school depending
                on the gravity of the offense.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-lg-3" id="myScrollspy">

      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1B">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> B. School ID </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>All bonafide pupils and students are required to wear their school ID properly at all times upon entering the
                campus, while in the school and during school activities whether on-campus or off-campus.</li>
              <li>The school shall strictly implement the “No ID – No Entry” policy. Any child who fails to present his ID upon
                entry may be issued an admission slip by the guidance counselor; however, habitual offenders shall be required
                to bring their parents upon notice of the guidance counselor.</li>
              <li>Mutilation, defacement or misuses of the school ID (including sharing with other pupils/students) are strictly
                prohibited. Damaged or lost ID shall be replaced through the guidance counselor office payment for a replacement
                shall be at the treasurer’s office only.</li>
              <li>The school guard or any personnel is authorized to confiscate the ID for reasons of truancy, show of disrespect,
                failure to follow instructions, improper uniform, rowdy behavior, destruction of school property, littering
                or vandalism. The ID shall be turned over to the guidance counselor, who shall request the presence of the
                parent/guardian prior to returning the confiscated ID.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-3" id="myScrollspy">

      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1C">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> C. School Security </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>The school guards are instructed to inspect bags, vehicles and other belongings of pupils, students, parents
                and other visitors who enter the campus.</li>
              <li>The following are strictly prohibited and shall be immediately confiscated: deadly or bladed weapons (including
                cutters), cigarettes, flammable materials, narcotics, prohibited drugs, explosives of any kind, alcoholic
                beverages, pornographic materials.</li>
              <li>For parents, guardians and visitors who wish to enter the campus for valid reasons:</li>
              <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha">
                <li>They must present any valid ID and secure a visitor’s pass from the school guard. The school reserves the
                  right to refuse entry to any person who refuses to comply with this rule or presents a threat to the school,
                  its personnel and the student body.</li>
                <li>They are not allowed to talk to teachers during class hours; instead, they must arrange for an appointment
                  through the Principal/Director’s Office.</li>
                <li>Any parent or visitor found loitering in the campus or disturbing teachers, even with the visitor’s pass,
                  will be escorted off the school and recorded in the guard’s logbook.</li>
              </ol>
              <li>Parents and guardians are reminded not to provide their children with expensive gadgets, jewelry and other
                items that may result in snatching, theft or even injury from undesirable characters outside the campus.
                They are requested to train their children not to use cellphones or other electronic devices during class
                hours, while walking along streets or riding transport.</li>
              <li>Untoward incidents must be reported immediately to school authorities. Parents are requested to visit the guidance
                counselor with regard to any problems related to school security.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-3" id="myScrollspy">

      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1D">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> D. Gate Pass Issuance </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>A pupil/student who feels ill may seek the permission from the subject teacher to go to the clinic. The nurse
                may issue a gate pass if the pupil/student needs to go home, but with the approval of the school director.
                Emergency cases need not be approved. However, the adviser/subject teacher must inform the office of the
                principal and director of such incidents.</li>
              <li>Permission to leave the school premises with gate passes issued by the teacher must have the recommending approval
                coming from the principal before it is brought to the director for approval.</li>
              <li>All gate passes issued by any office must be reported to the class adviser/subject teacher and the principal.</li>
              <li>All gate passes issued by any office must be presented to the school guard before leaving the school and must
                be signed by the fetcher.</li>
              <li>High school student are not allowed to go home during lunch break. However, students who live nearby may avail
                of a lunch pass from the school director.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
