      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1F">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> F. Attendance </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>All bonafide pupils and students are required to attend classes regularly for the duration of the school year.
                A child who incurs absences in excess of 20% of the number of school days for the year may be given a failing
                grade and no credits for the affected subjects.</li>
              <li>Teachers are required to call the roll before starting a class; any child who is not present during the roll
                call or remains outside the classroom in excess of 5 minutes upon the start of the class shall be recorded
                as absent.</li>
              <li>Any child caught outside the classroom during class hours shall be charged with truancy and given the appropriate
                disciplinary sanctions. The following are examples of truancy:</li>
              <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
                <li>Leaving the classroom without permission from the subject teacher or in-between class periods.</li>
                <li>Buying and eating in the canteen or loitering around the campus during class hours.</li>
                <li>Conducting club/organization activities without the permission of school authorities.</li>
                <li>Not returning to class after getting permission to leave from the teacher.</li>
                <li>Going to other classrooms to borrow things from schoolmates.</li>
              </ol>
              <li>Parents and guardians are requested to call the school if their child cannot attend classes. The school reserves
                the right to call any parent or guardian if a child does not come to school to confirm his/her absence.</li>
              <li>Upon returning to school, the child is required to submit an excuse letter to the class adviser, signed by
                the parent indicating the reason for the absence. The class adviser reserves the right to refuse to accept
                any child who does not submit the excuse letter, in this case, the child will be sent to the Guidance Office.</li>
              <li>If the child was absent due to sickness or hospitalization, the parent/guardian may attach a doctor’s certification
                to the excuse letter. If the child underwent an operation or was afflicted with a communicable/viral disease,
                the parent is required to submit a doctor’s certification that the child is fit to return to class. The school
                reserves the right to prevent any child from attending classes if no such certification is given and upon
                the advice of the school doctor. In such case, the parent shall be required to take the child home until
                further notice.
              </li>
              <li>Unexcused absences incurred before or after a weekend or holiday shall be deemed as a double absence and given
                the proper sanctions.</li>
              <li>A pupil or student selected for any activity sanctioned by the school shall be excused from attending classes.
                Teachers are required to provide the child with the necessary make-up work, special exams and other remedial
                activities for any schoolwork missed. However, the child must comply with such remedial measures within the
                deadline set by the subject teachers.</li>
              <li>The subject teacher is required to provide make-up work, special exams and other remedial activities for a
                child who was absent due to illness or other valid reasons as contained in the excuse slip. In the case of
                periodical examination, late examinees shall be given a 20% deduction in the raw score; however, no such
                privilege shall be extended to any child who skips classes for no valid reason or who cannot present an excuse
                slip for the absence incurred. In such case, the teacher shall refer the child to the Principal.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-3" id="myScrollspy">

      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1G">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> G. Punctuality </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>All bonafide pupils and students are required to exercise punctuality in attending their classes, school activities
                and gatherings. Punctuality shall also include the submission of classroom requirements within deadlines.</li>
              <li>Late comers shall be required to write their names, time of entry and reason for tardiness in a Tardiness Logbook.
                This Logbook shall be open for verification by parents/guardians during Parent-Teacher Meeting.</li>
              <li>Habitual latecomers shall be required to bring their parents/guardians to school for parent-teachers conference
                and imposition of sanctions including suspension.</li>
              <li>Late submission of requirements shall result in grade deductions or imposition of additional work requirements.</li>
              <li>In the case of field trips, those who are left behind are required to stay in campus until dismissal of class.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-3" id="myScrollspy">

      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1H">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> H. Medical Emergencies </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>The school clinic is open to all school personnel and the student body for medical emergencies. In case a patient
                needs to be rushed to a hospital, the school shall provide transportation to the nearest hospital.</li>
              <li>Medical bills for accident shall be covered by the pupil/student insurance plan. In the case of self-inflicted
                injuries or those willfully caused(such as fights or disputes), the offending child’s parents shall be responsible
                for all medical and hospitalization needs of the injured party.</li>
              <li>In case a child needs to be sent home, the school doctor, dentist or nurse shall issue the child a Gate Pass
                and contact the parent/guardian to fetch the child. The child shall not be allowed to go home by himself.
                The Gate Pass must be submitted to the school guard, who will course the pass to the Guidance Office.</li>
              <li>Parents and guardians are advised to inform the school of any relevant afflictions, medical conditions and
                prescriptions that the child will require so that the clinic may administer proper care when needed. </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-3" id="myScrollspy">

      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1I">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> I. Conduct Grading </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>All Sunbeamers are expected to exhibit good behavior and right conduct at all times, wherever they may be.
                Examples of desirable characteristics of a true Sunbeamers are as follows:</li>
              <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
                <li>Obeys school rules and regulations faithfully.</li>
                <li>Attends classes regularly and practices punctuality in all its aspects at all times.</li>
                <li>Practices courtesy, honestly, obedience and respect for all people, especially to persons of authority in
                  school.
                </li>
                <li>Waits for his turn by forming lines and does not demand service.</li>
                <li>Exhibits a cheerful and wholesome character/behavior.</li>
                <li>Carries with him dignity and restraint and practices good posture and clear speeds when he sits stands or
                  recites in class.</li>
                <li>Practices good grooming and personal hygiene, wears the school uniform properly and sports the correct haircut.</li>
                <li>Avoids unrefined and rowdy behavior, inappropriate display of affection, use of foul language and expressions
                  and disregard for the rights and opinions of their peers and their superiors.</li>
                <li>Observes sportsmanship in all forms of competition; humble in victory and cheerful in defeat.</li>
                <li>Promotes the proper use of school facilities and equipment, supports cleanliness in campus and observes conservation
                  of utilities such as water and electricity.</li>
                <li>Participates actively in school activities, exercising the spirit of cooperation, teamwork and leadership.</li>
              </ol>
              <li>Deductions to the conduct grade may be applied by the Guidance Counselor for infractions of school rules and
                regulations, including:</li>
              <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
                <li>1 point deduction for every unexcused absence.</li>
                <li>½ point for every 2 instance of tardiness.</li>
              </ol>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-3" id="myScrollspy">

      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1J">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> J. Collections and Purchases </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>All collections (for whatever club, organization or purpose it may serve) must be approved in writing by the
                Director. Any person who collects without proper authorization shall be given immediate disciplinary action,
                including suspension or recommendation for transfer.</li>
              <li>All transactions are to be coursed through the Directors Office only. No teacher, parent, visitor or child
                is authorized to transact on behalf of the school for any items such as t-shirts, magazines, books, supplies
                or equipment.
              </li>
              <li>Solicitations, borrowing of money and jewelry and extraction of favors of any kind by a teacher upon any child
                or parent are strictly prohibited.</li>
              <li>Projects and make-up work for academic deficiencies shall not include the purchase of books, materials, supplies,
                equipment, tools, food and drink, clothing or any other item not relevant to the subject matter.</li>
              <li>All projects that require taking trips, performing interviews or spending money must be approved in writing
                by the Director.</li>
              <li>Bribery of any school personnel is considered a grievous offense and shall result in immediate disciplinary
                action against the child, parent and personnel involved.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-3" id="myScrollspy">

      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1K">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> K. School Activities </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>All school activities (varsity, scouting, club/organization, and classroom) must be approved by the Director
                and require the presence of a teacher who shall personally supervise the activity. If the teacher is not
                available, the activity shall not be allowed to proceed even if previously approved by the Director.</li>
              <li>A Parent’s Permit duly approved by the Director and signed by the parents shall be required for all school
                activities, especially those performed off-campus or during non-class hours/weekends. Only those pupils/students
                with the affirmative permission of the parent shall be allowed to participate.</li>
              <li>Participation in field trips, camping and gatherings required by the school should be observed quickly.</li>
              <li>Any class, club or organization which needs to use school facilities such as the classrooms, Computer Room,
                Laboratory, TLE Room or Library must secure the written permission of the Director and be accompanied by
                a teacher-in-charge. They shall be held responsible for the cleanliness and orderliness of the facilities
                used. Any equipment lost or damaged shall be charged to them (including the teacher).</li>
              <li>If transportation is used, pupils and students must strictly observe bus assignments and practice the “buddy
                system” to look after each other. No child is allowed to transfer to another bus without the permission of
                the teacher-in-charge. Also, all participants must return to the school before going home. They cannot get
                off the bus while enroute.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-3" id="myScrollspy">

      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1L">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> L. Communications </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>Official notices and announcements from the school are posted on the school bulletin boards. Parents and guardians
                are advised to consult the bulletin boards periodically. Notices, posters and other materials cannot be posted
                unless with the permission of the Director. Unauthorized postings shall be taken down. Posting on school
                walls, doors and windows is strictly prohibited and shall be construed as vandalism.</li>
              <li>Official letters and permits from the school are normally coursed through the children via their class advisers.
                Parents and guardians are requested to fill up the acknowledgement slip and promptly return it to the class
                adviser. Failure to return the slip shall mean that the parent understands/agrees with the contents of the
                communique.
              </li>
              <li>Cellular phones and other electronic gadgets are strictly prohibited on campus.</li>
              <li>In case of emergency, pupils and students may request to use the telephone at the Director/Treasurer’s Office.</li>
              <li>Postal letters and packages may be coursed through the Guidance Office.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-3" id="myScrollspy">

      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1M">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> M. Periodical Examinations </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>All pupils and students are required to present a Test Permit before the periodical examination is given. Those
                who paid in cash shall be given a Permanent Test Permit valid for the entire school year.</li>
              <li>In conducting the periodical test:</li>
              <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
                <li>The child must have a test folder labeled with his/her name, grade/year & section adviser’s name to serve
                  as cover for test papers during the periodical examination. It must be clean and free for any unnecessary
                  writings for markings.</li>
                <li>All bags, books and other belongings are to be placed at the front of the room.</li>
                <li>The teacher shall strictly enforce seating arrangement.</li>
                <li>Silence is to be observed by all before, during and after the examination.</li>
                <li>Test schedules are to be observed strictly. No child is allowed to leave the testing room until the specified
                  time is met.</li>
                <li>The teacher may extend the time for a test, provided it does not exceed 20 minutes and is applied to all
                  the pupil/students taking the same test.</li>
                <li>The teacher may extend the time for a test, provided it does not exceed 20 minutes and is applied to all
                  the pupil/students taking the same test.</li>
              </ol>
              <li>Cheating is strictly prohibited. Any child caught cheating in any form shall immediately be given a test score
                of zero (0) and additional disciplinary action.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-3" id="myScrollspy">

      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-9" id="1N">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> N. Curfew and Off Limit Areas </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>All after-class activities such as CAT, practices, glee club practice and other authorized club activities
                must be conducted within the time and day schedule as approved by the School Director. Students are only
                allowed to stay up to 5:30pm.</li>
              <li>Pupils and students are required to vacate their classroom after classes and move to the school grounds (except
                when using library facilities).</li>
              <li>The curfew is 5:00pm, after which all pupils and students must leave the campus. Those waiting for their parents/guardians
                to fetch them may wait at the guard area. They are not allowed to loiter around the campus after curfew.</li>
              <li>No school activities shall be scheduled or allowed after the curfew period.</li>
              <li>No pupil or student is allowed in campus during weekends or holidays without the permission of the Director
                and must be accompanied by a teacher-in-charge. The school guard will not allow any unauthorized pupils or
                students into the campus.</li>
              <li>The following are off-limits to pupils and students:</li>
              <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
                <li>All Administrative Offices</li>
                <li>Faculty Room</li>
                <li>Stock Room</li>
              </ol>
            </ul>
