            <h4>
              <a> O. Suspension of Classes </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>As per DepEd Order No. 43,s.2012, classes shall be suspended as follows:</li>
              <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
                <li>When Typhoon Signal no.1 is raised by PAGASA, public and private pre-school and kindergarten classes in affected
                  areas shall be automatically cancelled or suspended.</li>
                <li>When Typhoon Signal no.2 is raised by PAGASA, public and private pre-school, kindergarten, elementary and
                  secondary classes in affected areas shall be automatically cancelled or suspended.</li>
                <li>When Typhoon Signal no.3 is raised by PAGASA, work in all DepEd offices in the affected areas shall be automatically
                  cancelled or suspended.</li>
                <li>In the absence of typhoon signal warning from PAGASA, localized cancellations/suspension of classes in both
                  public and private schools and work in government offices may be implemented by local chief executives
                  in their capacity as chairpersons of the Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management (LDRRMC).</li>
                <li>Parents are advised to check for media advisories coming from PAGASA, NDRRMC, LDRRMCs, LDRRMCs or the Office
                  of the President.</li>
              </ol>
              <li>Classes shall automatically be suspended after the occurrence of a fire or earthquake that directly affects
                the holding of classes. Parents and guardians are advised to wait for announcements from school authorities.</li>
              <li>In case suspension of classes occurs while classes are ongoing, the children will stay in class until fetched
                by their parents and guardians.</li>
              <li>In case suspension occurs on periodical examination day, all test schedules shall be moved to the day when
                classes resume.
              </li>
              <li>Parents and guardians have the ultimate responsibility for determining whether their children should go to
                school, even if no order for the suspension of classes has been issued, if they feel that travelling to or
                from school will place their children at risk.</li>
