            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>For Classroom Christmas Parties:</li>
              <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
                <li>The party must be conducted within the specified schedules – no extensions shall be allowed. Doors and windows
                  must remain open. Desks and tables cannot be removed from the classroom.</li>
                <li>Only enough food for participants should be prepared. The class adviser and officers shall oversee the quality
                  of the food. Alcoholic drinks are strictly prohibited.</li>
                <li>Personal audio equipment may be used, but a Gate Pass must be scored from the School Director. The owner
                  shall be held liable for damage to school property caused by such equipment, while the school shall not
                  be responsible for the loss or damage of such equipment.</li>
                <li>Rowdy, rough or lewd games are strictly prohibited.</li>
                <li>The room must be cleaned and set in a proper order at the end of the party. Trash must be segregated and
                  taken down to the trash area at the ground floor. Excess food must be disposed of properly.</li>
              </ol>
              <li>Birthday parties can only be held upon permission of the school Director and should never disrupt classes;
                thus, it can only be held during recess or lunch break. The school reserves the right to refuse a request
                for a party to be held for valid reasons.</li>
              <li>Parents and guardians are requested to serve only nutritious food and prepare enough food only for those who
                will attend; excess food must be brought home; spoiled food must be disposed of properly.</li>
