              <a> Q. Cleanliness and Orderliness </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>Cleanliness and orderliness must be observed inside the campus at all times.</li>
              <li>All pupils and students must practice conservation of water and electricity; thus, electric fans, lights, computers
                and air cons must be turned off when not in use.</li>
              <li>The following are strictly prohibited and shall result in disciplinary action:</li>
              <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
                <li>Littering and vandalism</li>
                <li>Unauthorized removal or movement, damage, loss and/or destruction of school property, such as desks, blackboards,
                  computers, electrical appliances and fixtures, tables and other equipment.</li>
                <li>Using personal electrical equipment like radios, CD’s and cell phone chargers.</li>
                <li>Playing rough games, loitering and hooliganism.</li>
                <li>Throwing of food, paper, sanitary napkins and other materials into drains, toilets and other plumbing fixtures
                  that may result in clogging of bowls and drains.</li>
              </ol>
              <li>Class adviser and officers must check that the room is clean and in order, lights and electric fans are turned
                off, trash is taken out and the blackboard, chalk ledge and eraser are cleaned.</li>
              <li>If a room is assigned/provided for use in extra/co-curricular activities, it shall be the responsibility of
                the teacher-in-charge, and/or club/organization officers to observe these rules on order and cleanliness
                of the room at all times.</li>
